Homepage goals

Communicate what you are in 5 seconds

Convert to newsletter with “Join Free”

Prove credibility with methodology and sources

Route visitors into SEO hubs: Insights, Neighborhoods, Tools

Stay fast and stable (Core Web Vitals)

Google’s Core Web Vitals targets to hit from day one: CLS under 0.1 and the CWV guidance is framed around stability and performance.

Technical and SEO constraints for the homepage

One H1 only

All nav and footer links are real <a href> links

Content is server-rendered or statically rendered

Hero image is decorative or small, never heavy

No layout shift on load, set image widths and heights to prevent CLS

Mobile-first, no hidden primary content behind accordions

Internal links support hub-and-spoke structure (home links to hubs, hubs link to articles)

Newsletter flow meets CASL basics, include unsubscribe and identification in emails

Homepage structure and copy
Section 1: Hero

Purpose: clarity + conversion

H1
Make smarter real estate decisions in Montreal

Subheadline
Local market context, neighborhood intelligence, and practical tools that help you decide with confidence.

Primary CTA
Join Free

Secondary CTA
Explore Market Insights

Micro trust line
Short weekly brief. No hype. Unsubscribe anytime.

Hero right-side visual
A lightweight “market snapshot” card stack (HTML/CSS, no heavy charts):

Inventory trend: Up, Down, Stable

Mortgage rate context: “Rates influence affordability more than most people expect”

Neighborhood highlight: “Verdun, Plateau, Rosemont, Griffintown”

Implementation notes

Avoid heavy imagery. Use a subtle Montreal photo only if it is optimized and sized, or use an abstract gradient and UI cards.

Keep hero under 650px height on desktop, 560px on mobile.

Section 2: What this is

Purpose: positioning without sounding like an agent

Headline
Not a listing site. Not a hype newsletter.

Copy
We built this for people who want to understand what is happening in the Montreal real estate market before making a move. We focus on signal, context, and practical decision support.

Three bullets

What changed in the market and why it matters

How neighborhoods differ beyond price

Tools that turn assumptions into scenarios

Section 3: How it helps

Purpose: value props, scannable

Headline
What you get here

3 cards

Market Insights
Clear explanations of trends, inventory, pricing, and buyer conditions.

Neighborhood Intelligence
How areas behave differently, who they fit, and what first-time buyers miss.

Practical Tools
Affordability, rent vs buy, cash flow, and closing cost scenarios.

Each card CTA:

Read Insights

Explore Neighborhoods

View Tools

Section 4: Weekly Brief preview (Primary conversion block)

Purpose: double down on Join Free

Headline
The Montreal Market Brief

Copy
A short weekly update that covers what changed, what it means, and what to watch next. Written to be useful even if you are not buying this month.

What is included list

A simple market snapshot

One neighborhood highlight

One decision scenario example

One thing to watch next week

Form
Email input + Join Free button

Compliance microcopy
No spam. Unsubscribe anytime.

Section 5: Featured Insights (SEO hub routing)

Purpose: push people into content clusters

Headline
Start with these insights

3 article cards

Montreal real estate market trends: what is changing and why

Rent vs buy in Montreal: a practical breakdown

What inventory shifts really mean for buyers

CTA
See all insights

Implementation notes

These should link to hub pages or cornerstone articles.

Each card has a category label, title, and a 2-line summary.

Section 6: Neighborhood Explorer preview

Purpose: local intelligence and SEO entry point

Headline
Neighborhoods are not interchangeable

Copy
Price is only one part of the decision. We break down the tradeoffs that matter: housing stock, walkability, typical buyer profiles, rental demand, and how the market behaves.

Neighborhood quick links
