Implementation notes

Tools pages should have content, assumptions, and explanations.

Tools are a natural backlink magnet.

Section 8: Methodology and sources (trust asset)

Purpose: credibility without bragging

Headline
Where the numbers come from

Copy
When we reference market data, we cite sources and explain assumptions. When we make a claim, we aim to show the context behind it.

Links
Sources and Methodology
Disclaimer

Implementation notes
Keep this section short on the homepage. The detail lives on /sources.

Section 9: Contact or “Talk to an Expert”

Purpose: high-intent path, soft sell

Headline
Have a specific situation?

Copy
If you are actively considering a purchase, sale, or income property, you can reach out for a practical conversation focused on your decision.

CTA
Contact

Section 10: Footer

Use the footer spec we already built, with the four links:
Privacy, Terms, Disclaimer, Sources.

Responsive design rules
Desktop

Max width: 1280px

12-column grid

Hero split 6/6 or 7/5

Section spacing: 72px between major sections

Tablet

Hero becomes stacked

Cards become 2-column

Mobile

Single column

Keep CTAs above the fold

Reduce large text slightly, keep line length readable

Homepage metadata spec (copy ready)

Title tag
Montreal Real Estate Insights and Tools | BrandName

Meta description
Clear market insights, neighborhood intelligence, and practical tools to help you make smarter real estate decisions in Montreal.

Open Graph

OG title mirrors title tag

OG description mirrors meta

OG image: a clean branded card, not a photo

Claude Code handoff checklist

Build as a component-based page with sections as independent components

No third-party sliders or heavy animation libraries

Prefetch internal links if your framework supports it

Make “Join Free” CTA consistent with navbar

Ensure no CLS by setting all image sizes and using stable font loading